-- Bogdanka, Orlen, Unipetrol May Be Active: Central European Stock Preview
-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 2010-10-29T03:59:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/bogdanka-orlen-unipetrol-may-be-active-central-european-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland’s  WIG20 Index  fell 0.1 percent and Hungary’s  BUX
Index  climbed 0.4 percent. The Prague Stock Exchange was closed
on Oct. 28 for a public holiday.  Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA  (LWB PW): New World Resources
NV of the Czech Republic starts a public bid for 100 percent of
Poland’s only publicly traded coal producer at 100.75 zloty per
share. Bogdanka gained 1.7 percent to 113.9 zloty.  PKN Orlen SA  (PKN PW): Poland’s biggest oil company and its
Czech unit  Unipetrol AS  (UNIP CP) are scheduled to report third-
quarter earnings. Orlen shares rose 0.2 percent to 39.9 zloty
and Unipetrol declined 0.5 percent to 194 koruna.  To contact the reporters on this story:
